article.headline: Ohio 70, St. Francis, NY 53
article.story: ATHENS, Ohio -- Jerome Tillman had 19 points and 12 rebounds to drive Ohio to a 70-53 victory over St. Francis, NY, Tuesday at the Convocation Center. Ohio (6-6) got off to an early lead and never looked back, building a 41-21 advantage by the break and a massive 30-point lead with 16:03 left in the game. St. Francis' Ricky Cadell dominated the Terriers' scoring with a career-high 30 points, but it wasn't enough to catch up to Ohio. Cadell also had six rebounds. Three of the Terriers' five starters did not score. Justin Orr and Tommy Freeman each added 11 points for Ohio, and Michael Allen had 10 points. The Bobcats hit a season-high nine 3-pointers with their 25th consecutive non-conference win at home.
